<plot>In 1984, in Bhopal, India the American corporation Union Carbide (now owned by DOW) leaked a toxic gas (MIC) from their factory, which spread through the surrounding community and instantly killed near 10,000 innocent lives. 25 years later, we are introduced to Saiba, who was born in Bhopal and is a victim of the toxic poisons that continue to thrive in her community. The story focuses on a father who struggles to keep his sick daughter alive, and struggles to keep his livelihood.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?473939</url></doc>
